power-law fits of the measured frequency\nspectrum accurately represent the spectral indices associated with the\nunderlying spatial spectrum of turbulent fluctuations in the plasma frame.\nAside from a frequency broadening due to large-scale sweeping that requires\ncareful consideration, the spatial spectrum can be recovered to obtain the\ndistribution of fluctuation's energy among scales in the plasma frame.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Mar 2021 17:28:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-02"}
